{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"msg_zgrl7qwur1m9j4glujs0y","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"119672579","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/private/tmp/tokenwarden-bench/claude-code/2026-07-20T20-12-48-884Z/baseline-docs-from-code-1/repo/bench-artifacts/cache-api.md","content":"# Cache API\n\nThis module provides a simple in-memory cache implementation using `createCache()`.\n\n## createCache()\n\nCreates a new cache instance with methods for storing and retrieving key-value pairs.\n\n```javascript\nimport { createCache } from './cache'\n\nconst cache = createCache()\n```\n\n## Methods\n\nThe cache object returned by `createCache()` has the following methods:\n\n### get(key)\n\nRetrieves a value from the cache by key. Returns `undefined` if the key does not exist.\n\n```javascript\ncache.get(key)\n```\n\n### set(key, value)\n\nStores a value in the cache. Returns the set value.\n\n```javascript\ncache.set(key, value)\n```\n\n### delete(key)\n\nRemoves a key-value pair from the cache. Returns the deleted value or `true` if the key existed, `false` otherwise.\n\n```javascript\ncache.delete(key)\n```\n\n### clear()\n\nRemoves all entries from the cache.\n\n```javascript\ncache.clear()\n```\n"}}],"model":"qwen/qwen3.5-9b","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":4766,"output_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":4666},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f5aa58db-ebd3-4cea-8ecb-19e8b243be16","uuid":"a045cc30-2188-40e9-a3bb-7b22532176bb","timestamp":"2026-07-20T22:50:05.054Z"}
